-- Cameron to Defend BP at White House Next Week Amid Gulf Cleanup, FT Says
-- Anchalee Worrachate
-- 2010-07-17T09:05:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/cameron-to-defend-bp-at-white-house-next-week-amid-gulf-cleanup-ft-says.html

          
          
             Prime Minister  David Cameron  will
defend BP Plc when he visits Washington next week, insisting the
 company  needs a stable future for the sake of the U.K. economy,
the Financial Times reported, citing an unidentified government
official.  
 BP Chairman  Carl-Henric Svanberg  met Cameron yesterday to
urge him to support the company after the oil spill at its well
in the Gulf of Mexico, the newspaper reported.  
